Remarks were made by Vice President Mike Pence at Andersen Air Force Base in Guam. He expressed gratitude and pride for the men and women serving in the Army, Air Force, Coast Guard, Marines, and Navy. Pence also brought greetings from President Donald Trump and highlighted the administration's commitment to the military, including increased defense spending and a pay raise for military personnel. He acknowledged the sacrifices made by military spouses and families and thanked them for their support. Pence concluded by wishing everyone a happy Thanksgiving and expressing gratitude for their service to the nation.